{
  "Question": "<p>Suppose <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_372\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> is an indefinitely differentiable real valued function on<span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_373\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"[0,1]\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </math></span> which satisfies <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_374\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{1}x^{k}f(x)\\,dx=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo rspace=\"4.2pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>\ud835\udc51</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_375\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=\\{0,1,2,3,...\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, prove <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_376\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> .<br/> My attempt :<br/> To prove this assertion , it suffice to prove <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_377\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{1}f^{2}(x)\\,dx=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo rspace=\"4.2pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>\ud835\udc51</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>  Then by approximation theorem , we can find a polynomial such that for every <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_378\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\epsilon\\gt 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>\u03f5</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\gt</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_379\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{1}f^{2}(x)\\,dx=\\int_{0}^{1}(f(x)-\\sum_{n=0}^{N}a_{n}x^{n})f(x),dx+%\n\\int_{0}^{1}\\sum_{n=0}^{N}f(x)a_{n}x^{n}\\,dx\\leq\\epsilon M\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo rspace=\"4.2pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>\ud835\udc51</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mrow> <munderover> <mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mi>N</mi> </munderover> <mrow> <msub> <mi>a</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>,</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <munderover> <mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mi>N</mi> </munderover> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msub> <mi>a</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mpadded width=\"+1.7pt\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </mpadded> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mrow> <mi>\u03f5</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>M</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_380\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"M=\\sup_{x\\in[0,1]}|f(x)|\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>M</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <munder> <mo movablelimits=\"false\">sup</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </munder> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> .<br/> It seems that we do not need the condition that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_381\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> is indefinitely differentiable , if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_382\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> is continuous then the conclution may hold .<br/> My question :<br/> a) Suppose <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_383\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> is a Lebesgue integrable real valued function on<span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_384\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"[0,1]\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </math></span> which satisfies <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_385\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{1}x^{k}f(x)\\ dx=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo rspace=\"7.5pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>\ud835\udc51</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_386\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=\\{0,1,2,3,...\\}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>3</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, can we prove <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_387\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> except on a set of measure <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_388\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>0</mn> </math></span> ?     </p> <p>b) If a) is not true , suppose <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_389\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> is a Riemann integrable real valued function on<span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_390\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"[0,1]\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </math></span> which satisfies <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_391\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{1}x^{k}f(x)\\ dx=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>1</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo rspace=\"7.5pt\" stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>\ud835\udc51</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span> for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_392\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=\\{0,1,2,3,...\\}\" displ